parameters:
Chancellor Shif: "Kukukuku... The time has finally come... The time for
Lord Xecily to be resurrected!"
Chancellor Shif: "Well then... This man is no longer of use... Die!"
Umi: "No way... Mia is... a person..."
Lutecia: "I am Lutecia... what you call a god... once one with Xecily."
Chancellor Shif: "What‼‼ L... Lutecia you say..."
Umi: "What... what are you talking about..."

Lutecia: "I have been waiting for this moment... Repeating the cycle of
life and death, so I could reach Xecily..."

Chancellor Shif: "Damn it... This is an unexpected turn of events... but no
matter... The vessel is already complete..."
Kru: "What... Umi and the others disappeared..."
Lutecia: "Kru... We must go as well..."
Lutecia: "This is the passage leading to the inside of Xecily's body."
Lutecia: "Xecily's body is sealed in another dimension."

Lutecia: "In your words, yes. And that man Shif is trying to resurrect
Xecily and summon it to this world."

Lutecia "That is... probably because he wants to use Xecily's power to make
all life in this world his own."
Kru "All life in this world... everything?"

Lutecia "Xecily is the god of life. With its power, it can impregnate all
living beings, and control all life that is born... just like children obey
their mother."

Lutecia "That's why I fought and split from Xecily in the past. And then I
sealed Xecily away."
Kru "Such... it's like something out of a fairy tale..."

Lutecia "I never imagined... that by scouring through the ancient texts,
one could actually resurrect Xecily... That man Shif is quite something."
Kru "...This is... too much for me to follow..."
Lutecia "It's not such a big deal."
Lutecia "...You swore... to always love Umi..."
Kru "That's!... That's because Umi was... with another man..."

Lutecia "Poor Umi... Umi was captured... taken hostage along with the
villagers..."

Lutecia "I warned you... but you failed to see through it... and you failed
to protect her..."
Lutecia "And you broke your eternal vow..."
Lutecia "Could you really not accept Umi... accept the changed Umi?"
Lutecia "Deep in your heart... there's still love, isn't there?"
